article.headline: James Madison 23, Towson 13
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Scotty McGee returned the opening kickoff 100 yards for a touchdown and Rodney Landers ran for two scores Saturday as James Madison defeated Towson 23-13. Landers provided most of the offense for the Dukes (8-3, 6-2 Colonial Athletic Association), running for 150 yards on 27 carries and going 7-of-12 for 71 yards through the air. His touchdown runs covered 18 and 23 yards. Towson (3-8, 1-7) had no yards on 28 rushing attempts. Sean Schaefer was 40-of-59 for 349 yards and one touchdown, a 16-yard strike to Marcus Lee in the fourth quarter. Demetrius Harrison caught 11 passes for 95 yards for Towson, and Rasheed McClaude had a 1-yard touchdown run. James Madison's Griff Yancey ran 15 times for 99 yards, and Dave Stannard kicked a 36-yard field goal.
